<quiz>
  <question type="stack">
    <name>
      <text>Finding the area of a triangular land using Heron’s Formula</text>
    </name>
    <questiontext format="moodle_auto_format">
      <text><![CDATA[<p>
A triangular piece of land has sides measuring {@a@} m, {@b@} m, and {@c@} m. Find the area of the land using Heron’s formula.
</p>



<p>
Give your answer correct to <b>2 decimal places</b>.
</p>

<p>
Area = [[input:ans1]] \(\text{ cm}^2\) [[validation:ans1]] [[feedback:prt1]]
</p>]]></text>
    </questiontext>
    <generalfeedback format="moodle_auto_format">
      <text><![CDATA[<h3>Worked Solution</h3>

<p>
The sides of the triangle are {@a@} cm, {@b@} cm and {@c@} cm.
</p>

<p>
Step 1: Find the semi-perimeter.
</p>

<p>
\[
s = \frac{a+b+c}{2}
\]
</p>

<p>
\[
s = \frac{{@a@}+{@b@}+{@c@}}{2}
\]
</p>

<p>
\[
s = {@s@}
\]
</p>

<p>
Step 2: Write Heron’s formula.
</p>

<p>
\[
A=\sqrt{s(s-a)(s-b)(s-c)}
\]
</p>

<p>
Step 3: Substitute the values.
</p>

<p>
\[
A=\sqrt{{@s@}({@s@}-{@a@})({@s@}-{@b@})({@s@}-{@c@})}
\]
</p>

<p>
Step 4: Simplify the brackets.
</p>

<p>
\[
A=\sqrt{{@s@}\times {@s-a@}\times {@s-b@}\times {@s-c@}}
\]
</p>

<p>
Step 5: Evaluate the square root.
</p>

<p>
\[
A \approx {@A_round@}\text{ cm}^2
\]
</p>

<p>
Therefore, the area of the triangle is:
</p>

<p>
\[
Area = {{@A_round@}\text{ cm}^2}
\]
</p>]]></text>
    </generalfeedback>
